# to make an analog clock.
--> We will make a hour, minute, & second hand.
--> At start, lets assume every hand is pointing at 12
==========================================================================
--> The hour hand will move 360 deg to complete one day.
			=> 12 hr = 360
			=>  1 hr = 360/12
			=>  1 hr = 30 deg
--> Meaning , it(hour hand) will move 30deg + some minute deg + seconds hand degree(we'll ignore this) to complete an hour.
			=> 60 min = 30
			=>  1 min = 30/60
			=>  1 min = 0.5 deg
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
=> for "h" hours, the hour hand will move 
			***********************
			=> h = 30 deg + m/2 deg
			***********************
==========================================================================
--> The minute hand will also move 360 deg to complete a minute.
			=> 60 min = 360
			=>  1 min = 360/60
			=>  1 min = 6 deg
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
=> for "m" minutes, the minute hand will move 
			**************
			=> m =  6m deg
			**************
==========================================================================
--> The seconds hand will also move 360 deg to complete a second.
			=> 60 secs = 360
			=>  1 secs = 360/60
			=>  1 secs = 6 deg
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
=> for "s" seconds, the second hand will move 
			*************
			=> s = 6s deg
			*************
			
